# Luckfox BSP cfg80211 compat shim
#
# The Luckfox 5.10 BSP (linux-luckfox.git) backports parts of the
# cfg80211 API that diverge from mainline 5.10. The aircrack-ng v5.6.4.2
# branch's recent kernel-6.x patches address this for mainline kernels
# but require a small additional shim on the Luckfox BSP to gate the
# `wiphy_ext_feature_set` and `WIPHY_FLAG_HAS_REMAIN_ON_CHANNEL`
# references on the BSP's kernel version macro.
#
# This file is a placeholder. The hunk lands once the rtl8812eu
# source is fetched on the first `make rtl8812eu-source` and the exact
# line numbers in `os_dep/linux/ioctl_cfg80211.c` can be confirmed.
# Until then the package is gated on `BR2_PACKAGE_RTL8812EU=y` so it
# does not break builds that don't select it.
--- a/os_dep/linux/ioctl_cfg80211.c
+++ b/os_dep/linux/ioctl_cfg80211.c
@@ -0,0 +1,1 @@
+/* placeholder: real hunk lands on first source fetch */
